webpackJsonp([0xdbcf92924524],{725:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>This is your week at a glance with metrics accumulation, gear totals, and activity data breakdowns.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Accumulation Charts stacks the days total on top of the past week for key metrics such as Distance, Elevation, and Time, as well as extended data such as TSS, Suffer Score, Kilojoules, and Calories.</li>\n<li>Gear breakdown shows you the accumulation of key metrics by gear.</li>\n<li>Comprehensive data breakdown for each activity.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; margin: 0.4em auto; max-width: 412px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 93.61997226074897%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Weekly Stats Chart"\n        title=""\n        src="/blog/static/weekly-stats-01-79a4f2eba81cef1cf1c85c52704d100f-31818.png"\n        srcset="/blog/static/weekly-stats-01-79a4f2eba81cef1cf1c85c52704d100f-b3e18.png 103w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-01-79a4f2eba81cef1cf1c85c52704d100f-571c4.png 206w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-01-79a4f2eba81cef1cf1c85c52704d100f-31818.png 412w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-01-79a4f2eba81cef1cf1c85c52704d100f-1be92.png 618w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-01-79a4f2eba81cef1cf1c85c52704d100f-05b5b.png 824w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-01-79a4f2eba81cef1cf1c85c52704d100f-17809.png 1236w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-01-79a4f2eba81cef1cf1c85c52704d100f-27003.png 1442w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </p>\n<h3>What does this do?</h3>\n<p>Weekly stats are based on metrics collected during a week’s worth of Strava activities. This gives you a quick way to see how your week is shaping up, as well as compare different metrics to each other. Touch any of the charts to show the value for that day.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Not all metrics are available to all users. A Strava Premium account is required for advanced analytics such as Power and Heart Rate. To find out more about that, visit Strava <a href="https://www.strava.com/premium/analysis" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a>. A Power Meter and Heart Rate sensor is also required for their respective data.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h4>Activities</h4>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; margin: 0.4em auto; max-width: 412px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 32.454923717059636%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Single Activity"\n        title=""\n        src="/blog/static/weekly-stats-02-674c694868356adfe7b8d3fa61e4595d-31818.png"\n        srcset="/blog/static/weekly-stats-02-674c694868356adfe7b8d3fa61e4595d-b3e18.png 103w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-02-674c694868356adfe7b8d3fa61e4595d-571c4.png 206w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-02-674c694868356adfe7b8d3fa61e4595d-31818.png 412w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-02-674c694868356adfe7b8d3fa61e4595d-1be92.png 618w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-02-674c694868356adfe7b8d3fa61e4595d-05b5b.png 824w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-02-674c694868356adfe7b8d3fa61e4595d-17809.png 1236w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-02-674c694868356adfe7b8d3fa61e4595d-27003.png 1442w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \nToggle the switch in under the Gear Totals for the week to see the Activities the Week’s Stats are based on.\n\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; margin: 0.4em auto; max-width: 412px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 89.32038834951456%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Single Activity"\n        title=""\n        src="/blog/static/weekly-stats-03-3ab2a820344dcbda28c7ec5cbd9e288a-31818.png"\n        srcset="/blog/static/weekly-stats-03-3ab2a820344dcbda28c7ec5cbd9e288a-b3e18.png 103w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-03-3ab2a820344dcbda28c7ec5cbd9e288a-571c4.png 206w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-03-3ab2a820344dcbda28c7ec5cbd9e288a-31818.png 412w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-03-3ab2a820344dcbda28c7ec5cbd9e288a-1be92.png 618w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-03-3ab2a820344dcbda28c7ec5cbd9e288a-05b5b.png 824w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-03-3ab2a820344dcbda28c7ec5cbd9e288a-17809.png 1236w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-03-3ab2a820344dcbda28c7ec5cbd9e288a-27003.png 1442w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </p>\n<p>To switch your measurement preferences in real time, use the Measurement Preference Toggle in the main menu, see (<a href="/blog/toggle-m-pref">this</a>) for more information.</p>\n<h3>What does this mean?</h3>\n<h4>Basic Metrics</h4>\n<p>Distance, Time and Elevation are available to all Strava users.</p>\n<h4>TSS and Kilojoules - Power Meter</h4>\n<p>TSS, short for Training Stress Score, also know as Training Load in a Strava Activity or Training Impulse on the Strava Fitness and Freshness chart (<a href="https://www.strava.com/athlete/fitness" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a>), is a number based on power produced and your current FTP. That looks a bit like this:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-js"><code class="language-js"><span class="token comment">// ET: Elapsed Moving Time</span>\n<span class="token comment">// WaW: Weighted Average Watts</span>\n<span class="token comment">// FTP: FTP</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>ET <span class="token operator">*</span> WaW <span class="token operator">*</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span>WaW <span class="token operator">/</span> FTP<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token operator">/</span> FTP <span class="token operator">*</span> <span class="token number">3600</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span>\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>FTP</strong>: A Race athlete uses your Strava FTP (<a href="https://www.strava.com/settings/performance" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a>). Keep this up to date for accurate statistics. Originally FTP was based on the amount of power an athlete could produce over an hour. Strava provides an estimate on the Strava Power Curve chart (<a href="https://www.strava.com/athlete/analysis" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a> ). If you have a few sufficiently long, hard outdoor rides, this number is usually close enough as a starting point.\nFor More on FTP see:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://www.trainingpeaks.com/blog/what-is-threshold-power/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">TrainingPeaks: What Is Functional Threshold Power?</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hDsN73cQpWc" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Global Cycling Network (video): How To Do A Functional Threshold Power (FTP) Test</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://support.trainerroad.com/hc/en-us/articles/201794984-20-Minute-vs-8-Minute-FTP-Test" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">TrainerRoad: 20 Minute VS. 8 Minute FTP Test</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Kilojoules is the power produced over the whole of the activity. It is closely linked with actual Calories expended.</p>\n<h4>Suffer Score and Calories - Heart Rate</h4>\n<p>Strava uses your Maximum Heart Rate and your ride data to determine a Suffer Score. You can set your Maximum on Strava <a href="https://www.strava.com/settings/performance" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here</a>. It is dependent on your Maximum being correct and you being in good health.\nCalories are based on your heart rate over the length of the activity and are not as precise as Kilojoules for measuring energy expenditure.\nThat said, if you don’t have a power meter, Heart Rate is the next best thing.</p>\n<h3>How can I make use of this?</h3>\n<p>One way to make use of this weekly data is to set weekly TSS or Suffer Score goals. Mind you, not all TSS or Suffering is created equal, but it can help if you are mixing indoor interval sessions and outdoor rides.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Power trumps Heart Rate, so use TSS if available.</p>\n</blockquote>',frontmatter:{title:"Weekly Stats",date:"2017-06-18T00:19:00.000Z",path:"/weekly-stats/",parent:"/home/hypersprite/Documents/code/araceathlete-gatsby-material-ui-v1/src/pages/blog-posts/weekly-stats.md absPath of file",tags:"newbie,power,results,training,activities,heartrate",description:"Weekly Stats has the info you need in one place",cover:{childImageSharp:{responsiveSizes:{src:"/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-7b166.png",sizes:"(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px",srcSet:"/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-32196.png 103w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-e3336.png 206w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-7b166.png 412w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-01e4b.png 618w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-0751a.png 824w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-832e5.png 1236w,\n/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-d700e.png 1442w",originalImg:"/blog/static/weekly-stats-cover-33dbd799663781ecaa9c69f4e3382028-d700e.png",originalName:"weekly-stats-cover.png",aspectRatio:1.5606060606060606,base64:"data:image/png;base64,"}}}}}},pathContext:{slug:"/blog-posts/weekly-stats/"}}}});
